The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The call MHD_DLOG(connection->daemon, _("The SHA-256 algorithm is not supported by this MHD build.\n")); passes a string literal (after translation via _) to a logging function. If MHD_DLOG (or the _ macro/gettext) is declared to take a non-const char * (common for some gettext implementations that return char * or for a logging API declared as char *), then the pointer is not const-qualified even though the function will not modify the string. That contravenes MISRA C 2023 Rule 8.13 (a pointer should point to a const-qualified type whenever possible).
